{
  "texts": [
    "Similar patterns of neuronal activity accompanied each blink, suggesting that the same mechanism generated them all.",
    "The cerebellum can thus use feedback from one movement as a cue to learn the proper timing of the next movement in a sequence.",
    "A key question is whether this mechanism of sequence learning extends beyond movement.",
    "The cerebellum has extensive connections to the brain's outer layer, the cortex, including many areas involved in cognition.",
    "Future experiments should test whether the cerebellum might help guide sequences of cortical activity during cognitive tasks."
  ]
}